    "where A 0 is the matrix transpose.",
    "We note that in the case k = 1, the definition of inflows and outflows correspond to the in-degree and out-degree of each node, respectively.",
    "But when considering longer paths (k > 1) the flow profiles describe the pattern of directional flows at longer scales and hence capture higher-order dependencies.",
    "We concatenate inflows and outflows up to maximal length k m for each node:",
    "where k m is a hyperparameter that defines the maximum path length, β = α/ λ 1 is a scaling factor, λ 1 is the largest eigenvalue of the adjacency matrix A, and α is a hyperparameter that controls for the variable weights of the short and long paths; normalization by the largest eigenvalue λ 1 ensures convergence for large k, in the sense that lim k!1 jjA kþ1 jj=jjA k jj ¼ λ 1."
